04/06/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- The final declaration to be released at the EU leaders' summit in Brussels later this month is expected to send an encouraging message about Turkey's EU membership prospects. 
According to local media reports Thursday (3 June), the declaration would commend the reforms that Turkey has undertaken, while underscoring the importance of full implementation over the next few months.
In other news, Turkish Justice Minister Cemil Cicek met with his Chinese counterpart, Zhang Fusen, in Beijing on Thursday. 
They discussed ways to strengthen bilateral relations and bolster co-operation, particularly in boosting security and fighting terrorism. 
(Hurriyet, Milliyet, Anadolu Agency, TRT 2 - 03/06/04)
